#30504
Red Square~
Being a socialist, Soviet was never one for extravagance, and his room
reflects that. You are in a very quiet, spartan chamber. Carved in one
wall is the image of a crossed hammer and sickle. Mounted on another wall
are several weapons, daggers and maces, that are the weapons Soviet once
used during his mortal life. The furniture itself is very minimal, a few
chairs for guests, a red sofa for Soviet to relax in, a table littered
with empty bottles labeled "Kahlua" and some rolled up pieces of white
paper with some odd brown and green herbs inside. While the room does
reflect the values of its owner in its modesty, you feel comfortable and
relaxed in it, almost as though it were a home away from home.
~
