#30532
Before the Glass Hotel~
You are now directly in front of the Glass Hotel; its doors are to your
west. If it seemed impressive from the gate, it seems twice as impressive
here. The hotel itself is a wonder. A cross between a cathedral and a 
greenhouse, this elegant building rises some fifty feet above the cliff-
tops, mounted on cast iron stilts and heated when necessary by a monstrous
stone furnace concealed in a kind of brass sarcophagus embossed with wolves
and cherubs. Lit from within by rows of torches burning with variously
colored flames, the whole edifice is made of glass, a mass of transparen-
cies and reflections that make it seem at times shiny and solid, at times a
ghostly mirage. Beside the door is a small bronze plaque, quite weathered
yet still readable.
~
