#30533
The Glass Lobby~
This is the lobby of the Glass Hotel. Fifty feet above you is suspended a
cut glass dome of incredible intricacy. The light in the room flows in
unusual patterns and colors, lending the large room a warped, surreal feel.
An enormous glass bowl in the center of the room contains water, in which 
are floating lotus petals and small purple candles. But the dominant
feature of the room is the massive staircase occupying its center. Made of
and unfamiliar, dark wood, it rises some twenty feet to the second floor
of this marvelous building. Elegant glass arches to the north, south, and
west mark the beginnings of corridors stretching in those directions. On
the western wall is mounted an unobtrusive silver sign.
~
