A Ballroom~
This enormous room appears to have once been a ballroom, judging from its
size and exquisite wooden floor, but it appears not to have been used as
such in some time. It is dusty and a thick carpet covers the center of the
floor. Cobwebs hang in the corners, and every footstep echoes loudly in the
high-ceilinged room. You wonder why this room seems so dim and abandoned,
while the remainder of the building is so immaculate. A hallway leads back
east.
~
