#30592
Billiard Room~
This room, while made of glass like the rest of the hotel, appears to be
made of darkly colored glass, possibly green, and further darkened by means
of thick, heavy curtains draped from ceiling to floor. It is smaller than
most of the other grandiose rooms you have seen so far. In it are an ancient
billiards table, three wooden chairs, and a small folding table placed
between the chairs. In the dim light, the corners of the room are largely
in shadow, and you are unsure what could be lurking there. You could explore
this room further, or turn around and head back north to the hallway.
~
